cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a new model for learning invariant representations in computer vision, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a learning algorithm. "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also highly likely as the paper deals with rotation-invariant feature learning in computer vision. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as the paper proposes a new neural network model. Finally, "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with natural language processing, but it is still possible as the paper proposes a new method for feature learning, which could be applied to text data as well.
